---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>Systems, C++, and Standardization</h1>
			<p>
				I am a member of WG21 (the C++ Standards Committee) and a systems engineer. This blog is where I share deep technical dives into C++, insider perspectives on the standardization process, and my thoughts on the evolving landscape of systems programming and build tools.
			</p>
			
			<h2>Current Focus</h2>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>WG21 Insider:</strong> Rationale and design process behind C++ proposals.</li>
				<li><strong>Catalyst Ecosystem:</strong> Building modern, AST-informed C++ tooling.</li>
				<li><strong>Build Systems:</strong> Why dependency graphs and build performance are still hard.</li>
			</ul>

			<p>
				If you're interested in the intersection of language design, compiler internals, and performance-critical systems, you're in the right place.
			</p>

			<hr />
			<p>
				<a href="/blog">Read all posts &rarr;</a>
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
